message.content:
Emily made a total of 9 designs using 63 cereal bits. To find out how many cereal bits were in each design, we can divide the total number of cereal bits by the number of designs:

Number of cereal bits per design = Total cereal bits / Number of designs
= 63 / 9
= 7

So, Emily used approximately 7 cereal bits in each design. It is likely that she used an equal number of cereal bits in each design since there was a consistent pattern of using 7 cereal bits for every design.
